# Type Hierarchy & Crate Boundaries

## The Canonical Hierarchy: Signal → Track → Identity

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Level 3: Identity                                                   │
│ Cross-document entity, may have KB link                             │
│ "This entity is Q7186 in Wikidata"                                  │
│ Type: anno_core::grounded::Identity                                 │
│ Contains: kb_id, canonical_name, embedding, source                  │
└───────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘
                                │ tracks linked via identity_id
┌───────────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Level 2: Track                                                      │
│ Within-document coreference chain                                   │
│ "These mentions refer to the same entity"                           │
│ Type: anno_core::grounded::Track                                    │
│ Contains: signals (Vec<SignalRef>), canonical_surface, entity_type  │
└───────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘
                                │ signals referenced by SignalRef
┌───────────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Level 1: Signal                                                     │
│ Single mention detection                                            │
│ "There's an entity here"                                            │
│ Type: anno_core::grounded::Signal<Location>                         │
│ Contains: location, surface, label, confidence                      │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Crate Responsibilities

| Crate | Purpose | Key Types |
|-------|---------|-----------|
| `anno-core` | Canonical types, shared across crates | `Signal`, `Track`, `Identity`, `Entity`, `MentionType`, `Gender` |
| `anno-coalesce` | Cross-document clustering, similarity | `EntityCluster`, `Similarity`, `HierarchicalClusterer` |
| `anno-strata` | Graph algorithms, community detection | `Leiden`, `Louvain`, `PageRank` |
| `anno` | NER backends, coref, evaluation | `Model`, `CoreferenceResolver`, `MentionRankingCoref` |
| `anno-cli` | Command-line interface | CLI commands |

## Type Mapping: Intermediate → Canonical

When building backends, always provide conversions to canonical types:

| Intermediate Type | Canonical Type | Conversion |
|-------------------|----------------|------------|
| `MentionCluster` | `Track` + `Vec<Signal>` | `.to_track(signal_id_base)` |
| `RankedMention` | `Signal<Location>` | `.to_signal(signal_id)` |
| `CorefChain` (eval) | N/A (eval-only) | Use for metrics, not storage |
| `CrossDocCluster` (eval) | `Identity` | Manual conversion needed |

### Example: Mention Ranking Integration

```rust
use anno::backends::mention_ranking::MentionRankingCoref;
use anno_core::GroundedDocument;

let coref = MentionRankingCoref::new();
let text = "John saw Mary. He waved to her.";

// GOOD: Get canonical types directly
let (signals, tracks) = coref.resolve_to_grounded(text)?;

// GOOD: Integrate with GroundedDocument
let mut doc = GroundedDocument::new("doc1", text);
coref.resolve_into_document(text, &mut doc)?;
// doc.signals and doc.tracks now populated

// AVOID: Using intermediate types without conversion
let clusters = coref.resolve(text)?; // Returns Vec<MentionCluster>
// These don't flow into GroundedDocument without conversion!
```

## Don't Confuse These

| Concept | What It Is | What It's NOT |
|---------|------------|---------------|
| **Signal** | A single mention detection | A cluster of mentions |
| **Track** | Mentions of same entity in ONE doc | Cross-doc entity |
| **Identity** | Global entity (may span docs) | Just a KB ID |
| **Entity** | General-purpose struct for NER output | Same as Signal (though similar) |
| **CorefChain** | Eval format for metrics | Canonical storage type |
| **Salience** | Importance ranking | Coreference resolution |

## Anti-Patterns

### Don't create orphaned types
```rust
// BAD: New type with no path to canonical hierarchy
pub struct MyMentionCluster { ... } // How does this become a Track?

// GOOD: Include conversion
impl MyMentionCluster {
    pub fn to_track(&self, ...) -> (Track, Vec<Signal>) { ... }
}
```

### Don't duplicate canonical types
```rust
// BAD: Redefining what anno-core already has
struct EntityMention {
    start: usize,
    end: usize,
    text: String,
}

// GOOD: Use anno_core::Signal or anno_core::Entity
use anno_core::Signal;
```

### Don't skip levels
```rust
// BAD: NER directly to Identity (skipping Track)
let identities = ner.extract_identities(text)?; // Levels 1 → 3

// GOOD: Each level has distinct responsibility
let signals = ner.extract_signals(text)?;      // Level 1
let tracks = coref.cluster(signals)?;          // Level 2
let identities = linker.link(tracks)?;         // Level 3
```

## When to Use Which Type

| Use Case | Type |
|----------|------|
| Storing NER output | `Signal<Location>` or `Entity` |
| Within-doc coreference chains | `Track` |
| Cross-doc entities | `Identity` |
| Evaluation metrics | `CorefChain`, `CrossDocCluster` |
| Salience ranking | `(Entity, f64)` pairs |
| Full document representation | `GroundedDocument` |

## Key Files

- `anno-core/src/grounded.rs` - Canonical hierarchy (`Signal`, `Track`, `Identity`)
- `anno-core/src/entity.rs` - General `Entity` type
- `anno/src/backends/mention_ranking.rs` - Mention ranking with Track integration
- `anno/src/eval/coref.rs` - Evaluation types (`CorefChain`, `Mention`)
